question: What was the time period in which the Duchy of Pannonia existed?

content.source_2: March of Pannonia The Eastern March () or March of Pannonia was a frontier march of the Carolingian Empire, named after the former Roman province of "Pannonia". It was erected in the mid-ninth century in the lands of the former Avar Khaganate against the threat of Great Moravia and lasted only as long as the strength of that state.
